SPRING

MODEL - VIEW - CONTROL
Buit on top of the Servlet API. This works with TomCAT (communicates through Catalina) which runs Servlets as needed.

Provides a way to develop RESTful web services - common requirement to open a host of RESTful end points for clients to access data.


JSP -->(Http Request/url pattern) --> Dispatcher Servlet -->Handler Mapping --> Controller <--> <--> <--> Calls Application Business Login --> --> DB
    <-- (Http Response) <-- View resolved

MODEL

CONTROL: @Controller
	Contains specific annotations

@RequetParam
@ModelAttribute - facilitates data binding. When you submit a form you have to convert the fields into a java object for processing as well as to display the values in jsp pages.
You can do this the conventional way using the JSP API - but you will have to invoke the request/ get parameter m